I'm rarely in Scottsdale, but I had meetings all day.
I asked a coworker where to go for lunch and he made the suggestion we hit up Big City Bagels.
I'm so glad we did.
I had a BLT Bagel to fulfill my bacon craving.
The bacon was crispy and there was plenty of it.
The sandwich was great, filling without being heavy.
The veggies were fresh and tasty.
The staff was friendly and I was quite impressed.
Now I'm looking for a reason to go back to Scottsdale for another lunch!

