From a girl who was spoiled by NYC bagels for 20+ years, I have yet to find a better bagel in AZ.
Einsteins, Lox, Stox, Chompies and most other are chewier and tougher, but Big City, is simply a big, soft bagel the way God intended it.
It's a small, straight-forward, no-frills store, hardly a wait, nice people, low prices and they just make the damn bagels right.
You should try it if you like bagels.
If you enter the shopping center from Hayden Rd.
you'll find it right away, as the store is on the back side of all the stores on Pima; roughly behind Staples.

