In my constant quest to find good bagels in AZ I came across Big City and figured I'd give them a shot.
The bagels are great!
Again, the salt bagels here don't have the rocky salt that I'm used to but this place does a nice job.
The salt, everything, poppy and onion are delicious and they have a Hawaiian, which I didn't think would be good but I ended up loving it (it has coconut and I think pineapple).
The cream cheese is very good and they put the right amount on, at least for my taste.
I like the fact that these aren't the pale bagels you mostly see out here, these are crispy outside with a nice toasty brown color.
Husband loves the weekend omelet sandwich.
Convenient location and parking - major plus.
I take bagels to go each time and I freeze them - these defrost and toast up great, another plus.

